# ðŸ”µ **1. API (Application Programming Interface)**

### **Definition:**

API ek system hota hai jo **do software applications ko aapas me baat karne** deta hai.

### **Key Points:**

* Data **mangne** aur **bhejne** ka tarika provide karta hai
* Developer ko server ki internal coding nahi pata hoti
* Sirf request bhejni hoti hai aur response mil jata hai

### **Unique Example (School Example):**

Socho school ka **reception desk** API hai:

* Student (client) ko certificate chahiye
* Reception (API) class teacher (server) ko message bhejta hai
* Teacher certificate bana ke reception ko deta hai
* Reception student ko certificate de deta hai

âž¡ **Reception = API** (middleman)
âž¡ **Teacher = Server**
âž¡ **Student = User**

---

# ðŸŸ  **2. JSON (JavaScript Object Notation)**

### **Definition:**

JSON ek **lightweight data format** hai jisme data **keyâ€“value pairs** me hota hai.
Ye human-readable aur machine-readable dono hota hai.

### **Key Points:**

* `{ }` aur `[ ]` use karta hai
* Fast & easy
* Modern APIs me sabse zyada use hota hai

### **Example:**

```json
{
  "studentName": "Aisha",
  "class": 8,
  "marks": [88, 92, 95]
}
```

---

# ðŸŸ¡ **3. XML (eXtensible Markup Language)**

### **Definition:**

XML ek **tag-based data format** hai jo data ko describe karta hai.
Ye HTML ki tarah dikhai deta hai.

### **Key Points:**

* Data tags ke beech hota hai
* JSON se heavy hota hai
* Purane systems me zyada use hota tha

### **Example:**

```xml
<student>
  <studentName>Aisha</studentName>
  <class>8</class>
  <marks>
    <mark>88</mark>
    <mark>92</mark>
    <mark>95</mark>
  </marks>
</student>
```

---

# ðŸ”´ **4. JSON vs XML (Short Notes)**

| Feature     | JSON                            | XML                |
| ----------- | ------------------------------- | ------------------ |
| Format      | Simple, clean                   | Tag-based, lengthy |
| Speed       | Fast                            | Slow               |
| Readability | Easy                            | Harder             |
| Data Types  | Many (string, number, booleanâ€¦) | Only text          |
| Use         | Modern APIs                     | Old systems        |

